                            3rd February, 1950. 
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                            <orgName key="Q1623362">The Hogarth Press Ltd.</orgName> 
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            <!-- recipient's address (add <addrLine>s as required) -->
                        </addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <salute>
                        Dear Mrs. Lucas, 
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    I am extremely sorry that your<lb/> 
                    letter of <date when="1950-01-21">January 21</date> has not been<lb/>
                    answered before.   Unfortunately,<lb/>
                    however, <persName key="Q703935">Mr. Woolf</persName>has had to go into<lb/>
                    a nursing home for an operation so<lb/>
                    I have not been able to show him your<lb/>
                    letter.   I am glad to say he is<lb/> 
                    now making steady progress and I will<lb/>
                    put your letter before him as soon as<lb/> 
                    he is able to deal with correspondence.<lb/>
                    It will probably be a month or so before<lb/>
                    he is able to come into the office.<lb/> 
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                       Yours sincerely,
                    </salute>
                    <signed/>
                    <seg>
                        <!-- post scriptum -->
                    </seg>
